---> app.component.html is the main page:
     @Component({
       selector: 'app-root',
       templateUrl: './app.component.html', --> link to html file
       styleUrls: ['./app.component.css'] --> link to css file
     })
     In this file, we declare variables to show on html file

---> Create a new component:
     Step 2:Update main template page
     Step 3:Generate new component
     Step 4:Add new component selector --> $ ng generate component my-teammate-list
     Step 5:Generate a SalePerson Class --> $ ng generate class my-teammate-list/MyTeammate
     Step 6:In SalePersonListComponent, create sample data
     Step 7:Build the table by looping data

---> Integrate CSS:
     Step 1:Get link for remote bootstrap files
     Step 2:Add link to index
     Step 3:Apply Bootstrap to html file
     Step 4:Apply Bootstrap to table
     Step 5:Update TS component file to reference bootstrap html template
